      "content": "fair enough. but even if it's not a panacea, it feels like the debate often ignores the fact that renewables alone might not be able to keep up with the sheer scale of the energy we need to replace all the fossil fuels. if the math shows we can't hit net zero without a massive boost from nuclear, isn't it kind of misleading to call it just \"one component\" as if it's totally optional?",
